Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Place potatoes in medium saucepan. Cover with water. Heat to a boil. Cover and cook 10 minutes over medium heat or until potatoes are tender. Drain. Place in mixer bowl. Add cream. Beat until potatoes are fluffy and almost smooth, using mixer at medium speed. Beat soup, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg. Stir into potato mixture. Spoon potato mixture into prepared crust and place on baking sheet. Bake for 1 hour or until center is almost set. Cool on wire rack to room temperature.